{
  "name": "editor4c: dragging an image reorders its block to the top",
  "_note": "Phase B — block drag-reorder via HTML5 drag-and-drop. The seed doc's <figure><img> is the 7th top block (index 6), immediately after the 'Image' <h2>. Images are draggable by default, so drag_and_drop starts a native drag on the img; the substrate dispatches real JS DragEvents (dragstart/dragover/drop/dragend) carrying a session DataTransfer to the editor's addEventListener handlers. Native DragDropState now survives the dragover/drop-line mutation; onDrop runs cmdMoveNode, dropping at the top so the figure becomes the 1st block. Verifies the reorder: the figure no longer sits right after the 'Image' h2, and is now the first top block while still present with its img intact.",
  "html": "test/html/editor-dom.html",
  "viewport": {"width": 900, "height": 700},
  "events": [
